&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Data Access and Disclosure Officer, Band 3&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;An exciting opportunity has arisen for a Data Access and Disclosure Office (DADO) Clerk to join our small but dedicated team.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;We are looking for an enthusiastic and organised individual with excellent communication skills to be able to work as part of this team whilst being able to work on their own initiative.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;The post holder will be responsible for the day to day work within the DADO team, including being the first point of contact on all matters relating to Subject Access Requests, responding to telephone, email and face to face enquiries and requests for information relating to Patient Records, processing these requests etc.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;The post holder is required to respond to requests in accordance with General Data Protection Regulations and The Access to Health Records Act 1990.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Full or part time/job share may be considered.&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Interviews will be held remotely on 18th November.&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;For further details contact:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Mia Reilly, DADO Office Supervisor&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;mia.reilly@SomersetFT.nhs.uk&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;01823 320456&lt;/p&gt;
